---
import BaseLayout from "../../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy";
const pageDescription =
  "How CVWriting.co.ke collects, uses, stores, and protects your personal data in line with the Kenya Data Protection Act, 2019.";
---

<BaseLayout title={`${pageTitle} – CVWriting.co.ke`} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="page-gap-after">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1 class="h1">{pageTitle}</h1>
        <p class="page-lead">
          This Policy explains how we handle your personal data when you visit cvwriting.co.ke or use our CV
          writing and related services.
        </p>
      </header>

      <p class="text-muted">Last updated: [insert date]</p>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2 id="who-we-are">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          CVWriting.co.ke (“CVWriting”, “we”, “us”, “our”) provides CV writing and related professional branding
          services to clients in Kenya and abroad. We are the data controller for personal data collected through
          the cvwriting.co.ke website, email, and our client onboarding process, in line with the Kenya Data
          Protection Act, 2019 and its regulations.
        </p>
        <p>If you have questions about this Policy or how we handle your data, contact us at:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: [insert data protection / support email]</li>
          <li>Phone/WhatsApp: [insert number]</li>
          <li>Postal address: [insert physical/postal address, Nairobi, Kenya]</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="scope">2. Scope of this Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, share, and protect your personal data when you
          visit or use cvwriting.co.ke, submit an enquiry or order our services, or communicate with us via email,
          phone, WhatsApp, or social media. By using our website or services, you agree to the practices described
          in this Policy.
        </p>

        <h2 id="personal-data-we-collect">3. Personal data we collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>
        <p><strong>Identity and contact data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Phone number</li>
          <li>City/country of residence</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Professional and CV-related data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>CV/resume and cover letters</li>
          <li>Employment history, roles, responsibilities</li>
          <li>Education and certifications</li>
          <li>Skills, achievements, professional summaries</li>
          <li>LinkedIn profile link and profile content</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Transactional data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Services ordered and package details</li>
          <li>Payment confirmations and transaction references</li>
          <li>Invoicing details (where applicable)</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Technical and usage data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>IP address, browser type, device information</li>
          <li>Pages viewed, time spent, referring URLs</li>
          <li>Cookie identifiers and similar tracking data</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Communication data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email and chat correspondence</li>
          <li>Feedback, testimonials, and survey responses</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          We do not knowingly collect sensitive personal data such as health records, political opinions, or
          biometric data. If you voluntarily include highly sensitive information in your CV, we will treat it with
          heightened care but may request that you remove it where unnecessary.
        </p>

        <h2 id="how-we-collect-data">4. How we collect personal data</h2>
        <p>We collect personal data through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Forms on our website (contact form, order/intake forms).</li>
          <li>Direct communication via email, phone, WhatsApp, or social media.</li>
          <li>Files you upload (existing CVs, job descriptions, supporting documents).</li>
          <li>Automated tracking technologies such as cookies and similar tools.</li>
          <li>Payment processors that confirm your payment and transaction status.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="legal-bases">5. Legal bases for processing</h2>
        <p>We process personal data on the following legal bases:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Performance of a contract</strong> – to provide CV writing and related services you request.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> – for certain marketing communications and optional analytics/marketing cookies.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> – to improve our services, maintain security, and manage our business,
            provided your rights are not overridden.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal obligations</strong> – to comply with applicable tax, accounting, and regulatory requirements.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="how-we-use-data">6. How we use your personal data</h2>
        <p>We use your personal data to:</p>
        <p><strong>Provide and manage services:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review and analyse your CV and professional background.</li>
          <li>Prepare CVs, cover letters, LinkedIn profiles, and related documents.</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about drafts, revisions, and delivery.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Customer support and communication:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to enquiries, complaints, and feedback.</li>
          <li>Send service-related updates and reminders.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Payments and administration:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Process and confirm payments via third-party payment providers.</li>
          <li>Issue invoices and maintain financial records.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Website performance and improvements:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Monitor website usage and performance.</li>
          <li>Improve user experience and content relevance.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Marketing (where permitted):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Send you curated content, service updates, and offers.</li>
          <li>Use anonymised or aggregated data for reporting and analytics.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You may opt out of non-essential marketing at any time by following the unsubscribe link or contacting
          us directly.
        </p>

        <h2 id="sharing-of-data">7. Sharing of personal data</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share it with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Service providers and processors, such as payment processors and mobile money providers, email and CRM
            platforms, website hosting and analytics providers.
          </li>
          <li>
            Professional subcontractors, such as vetted CV writers or editors working under our instructions and
            confidentiality obligations.
          </li>
          <li>
            Regulators, authorities, or law enforcement where required by law or to protect our legal rights.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="international-transfers">8. International data transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Our website and tools may be hosted or processed outside Kenya (for example, in the EU, UK, or US). Where
          this happens, we take reasonable steps to ensure that data is protected by appropriate contractual and
          technical safeguards and that transfers are limited to reputable service providers with suitable standards.
        </p>

        <h2 id="data-retention">9. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep personal data only for as long as necessary for delivering our services and managing the client
          relationship, meeting our legal and accounting obligations, and handling disputes and enforcing our rights.
        </p>
        <p>Typical retention periods include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            CV project files and communication: up to three (3) years after final delivery, unless you request
            earlier deletion (subject to legal obligations).
          </li>
          <li>Invoices and financial records: seven (7) years or as required by Kenyan law.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="security">10. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your data, including access
          controls, use of reputable platforms for communication and payments, and regular reviews of who has access
          to client files. However, no system is 100% secure. You are responsible for keeping your devices and any
          login details secure when accessing documents or communications we share.
        </p>

        <h2 id="children">11. Children’s data</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are aimed at individuals aged 18 and above. We do not knowingly collect personal data from
          children. If you believe a child’s data has been provided to us, contact us and we will take appropriate
          steps to delete or regularise it.
        </p>

        <h2 id="your-rights">12. Your rights under Kenyan law</h2>
        <p>
          Under the Kenya Data Protection Act and related regulations, you may have rights including the right to be
          informed, right of access, rectification, erasure, objection or restriction, data portability (where
          applicable), and the right to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.
        </p>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, contact us at [insert DPO/support email]. We may ask you to verify your identity
          before processing your request. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Office of the Data
          Protection Commissioner (ODPC) in Kenya.
        </p>

        <h2 id="cookies">13. Cookies and tracking technologies</h2>
        <p>
          We use cookies and similar technologies on our website. For details about the types of cookies we use and
          how to manage your preferences, see our{" "}
          <a href="/legal/cookies">Cookies &amp; Preferences Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 id="changes">14. Changes to this Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on
          cvwriting.co.ke, with the “Last updated” date at the top. Where changes are material, we may notify you
          via email or prominent notice on the website.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
